'''Generation 2000''' (G2K) is the young professional affiliate of the [[Jamaica Labour Party]] (JLP).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Helderman|first1=Rosalind|last2=Hamburger|first2=Tome|title=How Ted Cruz’s best friend drew him into Jamaican politics and business|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/how-ted-cruzs-best-friend-drew-him-into-jamaican-politics-and-business/2016/01/22/5bc43d90-bade-11e5-829c-26ffb874a18d_story.html|website=The Washington Post|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref> It is a center-right political youth organization that was founded in 2000 by a group of young professionals that saw a need for professional politics in [[Jamaica]] . The organization was incorporated as a corporate non-profit body, with a board of Directors chaired by Dr. David Panton in the year 2000.<ref name=":0" /> The current President of Generation 2000 is Stephen Edwards, a Civil Engineer and former University Lecturer,<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /> who is a graduate of [[Boston College]] and Florida International University.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ucj.org.jm/council-member/mr-stephen-edwards/|title=Mr. Stephen Edwards - The University Council of Jamaica|newspaper=The University Council of Jamaica|access-date=2017-02-20|language=en-US}}</ref>
