{{italic title}}
'''''The Rights of Minorities in the Islamic State''''' ({{lang-ur|Islami riyasat main zimmiun ke huquq}}) is a book written by [[Sayyid Abul Ala Maududi]], published in Lahore, [[Pakistan]] in 1954.

In it Maududi references the [[millet]] system and its organization along communal lines as a possible way the [[Islamic state]] would deal with minority rights according to the [[sharia]] concept of [[Dhimmi|dhimma]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cfr.org/content/publications/attachments/Nasr.pdf | title = International Relations of an Islamist Movement: The Case of the Jama’at-i Islami of Pakistan | accessdate = 2006-06-25 | last = Nasr | first = Vali | authorlink =  | coauthors =  | year = 2000 | format = PDF | work =  | publisher = Council on Foreign Relations | pages = 24 }}</ref>

